    "abstract": "<jats:p>I prove an envelope theorem with a converse: the envelope formula is \n            <jats:italic>equivalent</jats:italic> to a first\u2010order condition. Like Milgrom and Segal's (2002) envelope theorem, my result requires no structure on the choice set. I use the converse envelope theorem to extend to general outcomes and preferences the canonical result in mechanism design that any increasing allocation is implementable, and apply this to selling information.\n          </jats:p>",
